  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "T-cell mediated\nrash\nwith systemic features\n>90% of cases attributable to a medication (usually an antibiotic)\nMortality rate of ~5%",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "rash",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Rash"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Onset 1-5 days after starting causative medication\nRash\n:\nLarge areas of edematous erythema with numerous small, non-follicular pustules\nPredominantly affects main body folds and upper trunk, but can involve face\nNO mucous membrane involvement (in contrast to\nSJS/TEN\n)\nSystemic findings:\nFever\nLeukocytosis\n, specifically neutrophilia\n+/- Facial swelling\n+/-\nHepatitis\n+/-\nEosinophilia",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
